<% layout("/layouts/boilerplate") %>

<div class="container mt-5 mb-5 policy-page">
    <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
    <hr>

    <p>
        At <strong>Wanderlust</strong>, your privacy matters. This Privacy Policy explains
        how we collect, use, and protect the information you provide while using our platform.
    </p>

    <h4>1. Information We Collect</h4>
    <p>
        We may collect personal information including your username, email address,
        profile details, and any listings or reviews you create on the platform.
    </p>

    <h4>2. How We Use Your Information</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>To create and manage your account.</li>
        <li>To allow you to publish and manage listings.</li>
        <li>To improve user experience and platform functionality.</li>
        <li>To communicate important updates regarding your account.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>3. Profile Information</h4>
    <p>
        Information such as your username, profile picture, bio, and listings may
        be visible to other users. Your email address is never displayed publicly.
    </p>

    <h4>4. Image Storage</h4>
    <p>
        Images uploaded by users are securely stored using Cloudinary to ensure
        reliable hosting and delivery.
    </p>

    <h4>5. Cookies & Sessions</h4>
    <p>
        Wanderlust uses session cookies to keep you securely logged in while using
        the platform.
    </p>

    <h4>6. Data Security</h4>
    <p>
        We take reasonable precautions to safeguard user information. However,
        no online service can guarantee absolute security.
    </p>

    <h4>7. Contact</h4>
    <p>
        If you have questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact the
        Wanderlust development team.
    </p>

    <p class="text-muted mt-4">
        Last Updated: July 2026
    </p>
</div>